Abraham Sofaer ( October 1 , 1896 â€“ January 21 , 1988 ) was a stage , film and television actor . He was born in Rangoon , Burma ( now Yangon , Myanmar ) . He began his acting career in 1921 , on the London stage , but soon was alternating between London and Broadway . By the 1930s he was appearing in both British and American films , and appeared on television from its earliest days in the late - 1930s . Although his film appearances diminished after the 1950s , he continued to have guest roles on dozens of major U.S. television series throughout the 1960s until retiring in the mid - 1970s . Sofaer died in California as the result of congestive heart failure in 1988 . 